<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-699-952  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 699 952.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  August 30 1989 n114 p59(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mace Utilities. (Software Review) (Paul Mace Software Inc'sutility package)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Walsh, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Paul Mace Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Mace Utilities (Utility program) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationUtility Programs.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>It would be easy to think of Mace Utilities simply as a clone of the morefamous Norton Utilities - after aU, it includes sim- ilar safe formatting,disk sector editor and file and directory Undelete.andP;  Easy - but wrong,because this package includes much more.andM;Firstly, there's a vaccine, which if taken reg- ularly by your AUTOEXEC.BAT,is said to protect your disk from some viruses.andP;  There's a file to park yourhard disk's read/write heads at the end of each session, so that if somebodydrops your computer there will be less damage, and a nice little cache memorymanager.andM;Furthermore, if you go for the Gold edition you'll get special procedures torecover fragmented DBASE or text files, using knowledge of what these filesare supposed to look like.andP;  A straightforward set of programs will back upand verify your hard disk onto floppy disks  with all the usual options) andrestore as necessary.andP;  A routine which automatically saves your current RAMto disk every so often safeguards against power cuts and other nasties.andM;I saw no evidence to support the horror stories I've heard about Mace -although there is a long README file listing incompatibilities.andP;  The MUSE(Mace Utilities Sector Editor) runs without hassle and builds up the disk mapfile-by-file so that you can easily see where afl your memory is going.andM;Whether it's worth the price depends on whether you're likely to use thefacilities which Norton doesn't provide (most of them are also availableelsewhere).andP;  it also occupies a huge 1.5Mb of your disk.andP;  Wen worth a look,though.andP;  Norton's no longer on his own.andO;</TEXT></DOC>